ACS Wants Manfred Wennemer as Hochtief Board Chief, Welt Says

-- B y   R i c h a r d   W e i s s
-- 
2011-03-30T06:43:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-30/acs-wants-manfred-wennemer-as-hochtief-board-chief-welt-says.html
 Actividades de Construccion y
Servicios AS, the Spanish builder that is taking over  Germany ’s
 Hochtief AG (HOT) , wants Manfred Wennemer, the former chief executive
officer of Continental AG, to head Hochtief’s supervisory board,
 Welt  newspaper said, without citing anyone.  Hochtief’s annual shareholder meeting will vote on new
supervisory board members on May 12, and ACS wants four seats on
the 16-member supervisory board compared with two at present,
the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Richard Weiss in  Frankfurt  at 
 rweiss5@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Benedikt Kammel at   bkammel@bloomberg.net . 